03/michael-broadbent-mw-dies-aged-92/|website=The Drinks Business|date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Betty Williams (peace activist)|Betty Williams]], 76, Northern Irish political activist, [[Nobel Peace Prize|Nobel Prize]] laureate (1976).<ref>[https://www.lasiritide.it/art.php?articolo=18791 E' morta Betty Williams, premio Nobel e ideatrice della Citt\u00e0 della Pace] {{in lang|it}}</ref>\n*18 March\n**Sir [[John Tooley]], 95, opera administrator, general director of the [[Royal Opera House]] (1970\u20131988).<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tooley|first1=Sarah|title=Tooley|url=http://announcements.telegraph.co.uk/deaths/240281/tooley|website=The Telegraph Announcements|accessdate=20 March 2020|date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Kevin Taylor (rugby league)|Kevin Taylor]], 73, English rugby league player ([[Oldham R.L.F.C.|Oldham]], [[Leigh Centurions]], [[England national rugby league team|national team]]).<ref>{{cite web|last1=Baxter|first1=Trevor|title=Ex-Oldham ace Kevin Taylor found dead at home|url=https://saddind.co.uk/ex-oldham-ace-kevin-taylor-found-dead-at-home/|website=Saddleworth Independent|date=18 March 2020}}</ref> (body discovered on this date)\n*19 March\n**Sir [[Anthony Pigott]], 76, lieutenant general, [[Deputy Chief of the Defence Staff]] (2000\u20132003).<ref>{{cite web|last1=Pigott|first1=Anna|title=Pigott|url=http://announcements.telegraph.co.uk/deaths/240292/pigott|website=The Telegraph|accessdate=20 March 2020|date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Peter Whittingham]], 35, English footballer ([[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]], [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]], [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]]).<ref>{{cite news|title=Peter Whittingham: Former Cardiff, Aston Villa and Blackburn midfielder dies aged 35|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/11959208/peter-whittingham-former-cardiff-aston-villa-and-blackburn-midfielder-dies-aged-35|work=Sky News|publisher=Sky|date=19 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51928263|title=Peter Whittingham: Cardiff City legend dies aged 35|date=19 March 2020|work=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC}}</ref>\n*20 March \u2013 [[Mark Andrews (rower)|Mark Andrews]], 60, rower.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fasken.com/en/news/2020/03/inmemoriammarkandrews/|title=In Memoriam - Mark Andrews, QC|publisher=Fasken|date=21 March 2020|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n*21 March \u2013 [[Ted Graham, Baron Graham of Edmonton]], 94, politician, member of [[Parliament of the United Kingdom|Parliament]] (1974\u20131983) and the [[House of Lords]] (since 1983), [[Lords Commissioners of the Treasury|Lord Commissioner of the Treasury]] (1976\u20131979).<ref>{{cite news|last=Fortune|first=Joe|url=https://party.coop/2020/03/21/lord-ted-graham-of-edmonton-sharing-a-memory/|title=Lord Ted Graham of Edmonton: Sharing a Memory|publisher=Co-operative Party|date=21 March 2020|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n*22 March \u2013 [[Richard Sharpe (historian)|Richard Sharpe]], 66, historian and academic.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.wadham.ox.ac.uk/news/2020/march/professor-richard-sharpe-1954-2020|title=Professor Richard Sharpe (1954-2020)|publisher=Wadham College, Oxford|date=23 March 2020|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n*23 March\n**[[David Collings]], 79, actor (''[[Scrooge (1970 film)|Scrooge]]'', ''[[The Thirty Nine Steps (1978 film)|The Thirty Nine Steps]]'', ''[[The Invisible Woman (2013 film)|The Invisible Woman]]'').<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scifibulletin.com/2020/03/23/rip-david-collings/|title=RIP David Collings|publisher=SciFi Bulletin|date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Tristan Garel-Jones]], 79, politician, [[Member of Parliament|MP]] (1979\u20131997), [[Minister for Europe]] (1990\u20131993) and [[Treasurer of the Household]] (1989\u20131990).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/obituaries/2020/03/24/tristan-garel-jonestory-wet-able-deputy-chief-whip-margaret/|title=Tristan Garel-Jones, Tory 'wet' and able deputy chief whip under Margaret Thatche