ne Bridges]], 83, professional wrestler ([[All Star Wrestling|ASW]]).<ref>{{cite web|author1=H Jenkins|title=UK Pro Wrestling Veteran Wayne Bridges Passes Away|url=https://www.ringsidenews.com/2020/03/09/uk-pro-wrestling-veteran-wayne-bridges-passes-away/|website=Ringside News|accessdate=11 March 2020|date=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Ernest Davies (Stretford MP)|Ernest Davies]], 93, politician, [[Member of Parliament|MP]] (1966\u20131970).<ref>{{cite web|title=Announcing the passing of Ernest Dr DAVIES|url=https://funeral-notices.co.uk/coventry%20telegraph/death-notices/notice/davies/4823919|website=Coventry Telegraph|accessdate=20 March 2020|date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n*9 March\n**[[Richard K. Guy]], 103, mathematician (''[[Winning Ways for your Mathematical Plays]]'', [[Strong Law of Small Numbers]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://science.ucalgary.ca/mathematics-statistics/about/richard-guy|title=Remembering Richard Guy: 1916\u20132020| publisher=[[University of Calgary]]|date=10 March 2020|accessdate=10 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Canadian Climbing Legend Richard Guy Dies at 103|url=https://gripped.com/news/canadian-climbing-legend-richard-guy-dies-at-103/|website=Gripped|date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n**[[George Strachan (Scottish cricketer)|George Strachan]], 87, Scottish cricketer ([[Scotland national cricket team|national team]]).<ref>{{cite web|title=George Strachan|url=http://www.eastleague.org.uk/news/george-strachan/|website=East League|date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n*11 March \u2013 [[Michel Roux]], 78, French-born chef and restaurateur ([[Le Gavroche]], [[The Waterside Inn]]), [[idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis]].<ref>{{cite news |date= 12 March 2020 |title= Michel Roux: French restaurateur and chef dies aged 78 |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-berkshire-51856312 |work= BBC News |access-date= 14 March 2020}}</ref>\n*12 March\n**Sir [[John Chalstrey]], 88, surgeon and civic leader, [[Lord Mayor of London]] (1995\u20131996).<ref>{{cite web|last1