d|Digital download]]\n|-\n|United States<ref name=\"US Digital\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/a-year-without-rain-single/id387935992|title=A Year Without Rain \u2013 Single by Selena Gomez & the Scene|work=iTunes|publisher=Apple, Inc|accessdate=2010-09-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|Australia<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/a-year-without-rain/id390870569?i=390870584&ign-mpt=uo%3D4|title=A Year Without Rain \u2013 Single by Selena Gomez & the Scene (Australia)|work=iTunes|publisher=Apple, Inc|accessdate=2010-09-19}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"10\"|September 17, 2010\n|-\n|Belgium<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/be/album/a-year-without-rain/id390870569?i=390870584&ign-mpt=uo%3D4|title=A Year Without Rain \u2013 Single by Selena Gomez & the Scene (Belgium)|work=iTunes|publisher=Apple, Inc|accessdate=2010-09-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|Denmark<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/dk/album/a-year-without-rain/id390870569?i=390870584&ign-mpt=uo%3D4|title=A Year Without Rain \u2013 Single by Selena Gomez & the Scene (Denmark)|work=iTunes|publisher=Apple, Inc|accessdate=2010-09-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|Finland<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/fi/album/a-year-without-rain/id390870569?i=390870584&ign-mpt=uo%3D4|title=A Year Without Rain \u2013 Single by Selena Gomez & the Scene (Finland)|work=iTunes|publisher=Apple, Inc|accessdate=2010-09-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|France<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/fr/album/a-year-without-rain/id390870569?i=390870584&ign-mpt=uo%3D4|title=A Year Without Rain \u2013 Single by Selena Gomez & the Scene (France)|work=iTunes|publisher=Apple, Inc|accessdate=2010-09-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|New Zealand<ref name=\"Digital\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/nz/album/a-year-without-rain/id390870569?i=390870584&ign-mpt=uo%3D4|title=A Year Without Rain \u2013 Single by Selena Gomez & the Scene (New Zealand)|work=iTunes|publisher=Apple, Inc|accessdate=2010-09-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|Portugal<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/pt/album/a-year-without-rain/id390870569?i=390870584&ign-mpt=uo%3D4|title=A Year Without Rain \u2013 Single by Selena Gomez & the Scene (Portugal)|work=iTunes|publisher=Apple, Inc|accessdate=2010-09-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|Spain<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/se/album/a-year-without-rain-single/id390870569|title=A Year Without Rain \u2013 Single by Selena Gomez & the Scene (Spain)|work=iTunes|publisher=Apple, Inc|accessdate=2010-09-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|Sweden<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/es/album/a-year-without-rain/id390870569?i=390870584&ign-mpt=uo%3D4|title=A Year Without Rain \u2013 Single by Selena Gomez & the Scene (Sweden)|work=iTunes|publisher=Apple, Inc|accessdate=2010-09-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|Switzerland<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ch/album/a-year-without-rain/id390870569?i=390870584&ign-mpt=uo%3D4|title=A Year Without Rain \u2013 Single by Selena Gomez & the Scene (Switzerland)|work=iTunes|publisher=Apple, Inc|accessdate=2010-09-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|Germany<ref name=\"CD\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.de/dp/B0048IDRAK |title=A Year Without Rain \u2013 Single by Selena Gomez & the Scene (Germany)|publisher=[[Amazon.com|Amazon.de]]|language=German|accessdate=2010-10-24}}</ref>\n|November 12, 2010\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Compact Disc single|CD single]]\n|-\n|United Kingdom<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B0048IDRAK/|title=A Year Without Rain: Selena Gomez|publisher=[[Amazon.com|Amazon.co.uk]]|accessdate=2011-11-13}}</ref>\n|November 22, 2010\n|-\n|Taiwan\n|October 24, 2010\n|[[Music download|Digital download]]\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*  [[List of number-one dance singles of 2011 (U.S.)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Selena Gomez & the Scene}}\n\n{{Good article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Year Without Rain (song)}}\n[[Category:2010 singles]]\n[[Category:Synth-pop ballads]]\n[[Category:Selena Gomez & the Scene songs]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language songs]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Toby Gad]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Lindy Robbins]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Toby Gad]]\n[[Category:Eurodance songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance Club Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Hollywood Records singles]]\n[[Category:2010 songs]]\n[[Category:2010s ballads]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = A Year Without Rain\n| cover      = Selena Gomez & the Scene - A Year Without Rain (single cover).jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Selena Gomez & the Scene]]\n| album      = [[A Year Without Rain]]\n| released   = {{start date|2010|09|07}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[CD single]]}}\n| recorded   = April 13, 2010\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Electro (music)|Electro]]|[[Eurodance]]|[[synth-pop]]}}\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=54}}\n| label      = [[Hollywood Records|Hollywood]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Lindy Robbins]]|[[Toby Gad]]}}\n| producer   = Toby Gad\n| chronology = [[Selena Gomez & the Scene]]\n| prev_title = [[Live Like There's No Tomorrow]]\n| prev_year  = 2010\n| next_title = [[Un A\u00f1o Sin Lluvia]]\n| next_year  = 2010\n| misc       = {{External music video|1=[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M8uPvX2te0I \"A Year Without Rain\"]<br>on [[YouTube]]<br>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vaoPovB40dQ \"Un A\u00f1o Sin Lluvia\"]<br>on [[YouTube]]}}\n}}\n\n\"'''A Year Without Rain'''\" is a song by American band [[Selena Gomez & the Scene]]. It was written by [[Lindy Robbins]] and [[Toby Gad]], with the latter also producing the song. The song was released on September 7, 2010 as the second and final single from the band's [[A Year Without Rain|second album of the same name]]. A Spanish-language version of the song was also recorded, entitled \"'''Un A\u00f1o Sin Lluvia'''\" {{IPA-es|un \u02c8a\u0272o si\u0272 \u02c8\u028eu\u03b2ja|}}. Gomez titled the album for the song because she wanted to base all the other songs around it. Musically, the song is a [[Eurodance]] track backed with a [[disco]] beat. In its lyrics, the song's protagonist compares yearning for her love to a year without rain.\n\nMusic critics gave the song positive reviews, complimenting it as a dance ballad and noting Gomez's vocal maturity. \"A Year Without Rain\" became the band's third consecutive top forty single in the United States and Canada. It also charted in the lower regions of some European countries. The song is [[Music recording certification|certified]] Double Platinum in the US. The song's accompanying music video, directed by Chris Dooley and shot on-site in [[Lucerne Valley, California]] features Gomez frolicking in the desert surrounded by a swarm of photographs of her and her love interest, before they meet during a rainstorm. The band performed the song a number of times via live performances, including on televised programs such as ''[[Good Morning America]]'', ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'', and the [[37th People's Choice Awards|2011 People's Choice Awards]].\n\n==Background and composition==\n{{listen\n| filename    = SelGomez AYearWithoutRain.ogg\n| pos         = left\n| title       = \"A Year Without Rain\"\n| description = A sample of \"A Year Without Rain\", a [[Eurodance]] track which utilizes a [[disco]] backing.\n| format      = [[Ogg]]\n}}\nIn early 2010, a demo of the song, performed by singer [[RaVaughn]] leaked online. Becky Bain of Idolator called the song a \"mature dance track\" and said that it \"wouldn\u2019t entirely be out of place on a [[Sophie Ellis-Bextor]] album.\"<ref name=\"Alexa\">{{cite web|url=http://idolator.com/5591471/selena-gomez-goes-a-year-without-rain-on-new-dance-track|title=Selena Gomez Goes \"A Year Without Rain\" On New Dance Track \u2014 Hear A Demo|first=Becky|last=Bain|work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|accessdate=2010-12-27}}</ref>\nIt seems that it was first made for Leona Lewis.\nIn an interview with [[MTV News]], Gomez said that \"A Year Without Rain\" was the first song she recorded for the album.<ref name=\"VenaInsp\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1648277/20100920/gomez__selena.jhtml|title=Selena Gomez Says Fans Inspired A Year Without Rain|first=Jocelyn|last=Vena|accessdate=2010-12-26|work=[[MTV News]]|publisher=[[MTV Networks]] (Viacom)|date=2010-09-21}}</ref> She also explained why she named the album for the song, commenting, \"I feel like that song has a lot of meaning, and it also kind of was the start of what I wanted to base all the other songs around.\"<ref name=\"VenaInsp\"/> A [[Spanish-language]] version of the song titled \"Un A\u00f1o Sin Lluvia\" was released through the [[iTunes Store]] on October 26, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/mx/album/un-ano-sin-lluvia-spanish/id398033076|title=Un A\u00f1o Sin Lluvia (Spanish Version) \u2013 Single by Selena Gomez & The Scene|work=[[iTunes Store|iTunes Store Mexico]]|publisher=[[Apple Inc]]|accessdate=2011-03-15}}</ref>\n\n\"A Year Without Rain\" was written by [[Lindy Robbins]] and [[Toby Gad]], the later also producing it, with a length of three minutes and twenty-nine seconds.<ref name=\"Vick\"/> Musically, it has been described as a [[Dance music|dance]] track,<ref name=\"Alexa\"/> more especifically as [[Eurodance]].<ref name=\"musicOMH\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musicomh.com/albums/selena-gomez_0910.htm |title=Selena Gomez & The Scene \u2013 A Year Without Rain |publisher=[[musicOMH]] |last=Welsh |first=David |accessdate=2011-11-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101207094247/http://www.musicomh.com/albums/selena-gomez_0910.htm |archivedate=2010-12-07 }}</ref> It has also been called a [[synth-pop]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.chron.com/rodeoblog/2011/03/selena-gomez-brings-pop-sparkle-to-rodeohouston/|title=Selena Gomez brings pop sparkle to RodeoHouston|work=[[Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo|Houston Rodeo]]|accessdate=August 12, 2015}}</ref> and [[Electro (music)|electro]] track<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/playlist/selena-gomez-next-steps/pl.d9d329bbccfe44f0866f73399bea1342|title=Selena Gomez: Next Steps|work=[[Apple Music]], [[iTunes]] (US)}}</ref> which uses a standard [[Pop music|pop]] structure and is backed with a [[disco]] beat.<ref name=\"Vick\"/> According to sheet music published at Musicnotes.com by [[EMI Music Publishing]], \"A Year Without Rain\" is set in [[common time]] and has a tempo of 120 [[tempo (music)|beats per minute]].<ref name=\"sheet\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtdFPE.asp?ppn=MN0087107|title=Selena Gomez \u2013 A Year Without Rain \u2013 Sheet Music|work=Musicnotes.com|publisher=[[Alfred Publishing]]|accessdate=2010-12-26}}</ref> It is written in the [[Key (music)|key]] of [[Mixolydian mode|C Mixolydian]] and follows the [[chord progression]] of C\u2013Gm\u2013Dm\u2013F throughout most of the song, but the [[Bridge (music)|Bridge]] is written in [[D minor|D Minor]], following a chord progression of Bb-C-Am-Dm.<ref name=\"sheet\"/> It's important to mention that C Mixolydian and D Minor share the same [[key signature]], so the [[musical note]]s of both [[Mode (music)|modes]] are the same, but the [[Tonic (music)|tonic note]] is different.<ref name=\"sheet\" /> Gomez's vocals in the song span from F<sub>3</sub> to E<sub>5</sub>.<ref name=\"sheet\"/> Lyrically, the song sees Gomez longing for the object of her affection and compares it to a year without rain: \"I need you by my side/ Don't know how I'll survive/A day without you is like a year without rain.\"<ref name=\"Vick\"/> According to Megan Vick of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', the sound of the song contrasts with its \"tender\" lyrics.<ref name=\"Vick\"/>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical reception===\nAlthough he called it one of the album's \"pensive moments\", Bill Lamb of [[About.com]] noted the track as one of the top songs on the album, calling it a \"beautiful dance ballad.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://top40.about.com/od/albums/fr/Selena-Gomez-And-The-Scene-A-Year-Without-Rain.htm|title=Selena Gomez and the Scene - A Year Without Rain|work=About.com|publisher=The New York Times Company|accessdate=2010-12-26|first=Bill|last=Lamb}}</ref> Lamb also said the song shows \"Selena Gomez is clearly growing up as an artist.\"<ref name=\"LambVideo\">{{cite web|url=http://top40.about.com/b/2010/09/06/selena-gomez-a-year-without-rain-video-introduces-elegant-dance-ballad.htm|title=Selena Gomez \"A Year Without Rain\" Video Introduces Elegant Dance Ballad|first=Bill|last=Lamb|accessdate=2010-12-27|work=[[About.com]]|publisher=[[The New York Times Company]]|date=2010-09-06}}</ref> Stating that it showed her \"maturation as an artist\", Lamb later ranked the song number thirty-nine on the site's list of \"Top 100 Pop Songs of 2010\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://top40.about.com/od/top10lists/tp/top100songs2010.01.htm|title=Top 100 Pop Songs of 2010 - List of the 100 Best Songs of the Year|work=About.com|accessdate=2010-12-31|first=Bill|last=Lamb|publisher=The New York Times Company}}</ref> [[Allmusic]]'s Tim Sendra also named the song a standout on the album, calling it \"catchy\" and \"well-sung\".<ref name=\"Sendra\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/a-year-without-rain-r1955339/review|title=A Year Without Rain \u2013 Selena Gomez & the Scene|first=Tim|last=Sendra|accessdate=2010-12-26|work=[[Allmusic]]|publisher=[[Rovi Corporation]]}}</ref> Megan Vick of ''Billboard'' said that while Gomez did not have the vocal power of [[Demi Lovato]], she \"makes a strong effort to attack the high notes as she croons the chorus\".<ref name=\"Vick\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/review/1068589/selena-gomez-the-scene-a-year-without-rain|title=Selena Gomez & The Scene, \"A Year Without Rain\"|first=Megan|last=Vick|accessdate=2010-12-26|date=2010-10-01|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|location=[[New York City]]}}</ref> Vick stated that the song \"is compelling enough to separate the singer from other Disney-groomed pop stars.\"<ref name=\"Vick\"/> ''[[Wairarapa Times-Age]]'' writer Kim Gillespie named \"A Year Without Rain\" one of the album's highlights.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.times-age.co.nz/news/album-review-year-without-rain-selena-gomez/1033742/|date=2010-11-19|title=Album Review: A Year Without Rain \u2013 Selena Gomez & The Scene|work=[[Wairarapa Times-Age]]|publisher=[[APN News & Media]]|last=Gillespie|first=Kim|accessdate=2011-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120312225541/http://www.times-age.co.nz/news/album-review-year-without-rain-selena-gomez/1033742/|archive-date=2012-03-12|url-status=dead}}</ref> David Welsh of [[musicOMH]] noted Gomez' mature performance and wrote that the song \"reaps rewards with an impressively heartbroken stab at euro-dance\".<ref name=\"musicOMH\"/> In contrast, ''[[The Washington Post]]'' critic Allison Stewart was unfavorable of the lyrical content of the song, commenting that it was \"the sort of exercise in teenage co-dependence...that should be long extinct.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.washingtonpost.com/clicktrack/2010/09/album_review_selena_gomez_a_ye.html |title=Album review: Selena Gomez, \"A Year Without Rain\" |work=[[The Washington Post]] |publisher=[[The Washington Post Company]] |accessdate=2010-12-26 |first=Allison |last=Stewart |date=2010-09-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120511205242/http://blog.washingtonpost.com/clicktrack/2010/09/album_review_selena_gomez_a_ye.html |archivedate=2012-05-11 }}</ref>\n\n===Chart performance===\nPropelled by its debut at number fourteen on the [[Hot Digital Songs]] chart, \"A Year Without Rain\" debuted at number thirty-five on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], becoming the group's third consecutive top forty single.<ref name=\"sc_Billboardhot100_Selena Gomez\"/> It remained on the chart for four weeks.<ref name=\"sc_Billboardhot100_Selena Gomez\"/> On the week dated January 1, 2011, the song debuted at number thirty-six on the US [[Hot Dance Club Songs|Hot Dance Club Play]] chart.<ref name=\"sc_Billboarddanceclubplay_Selena Gomez\"/> As of August 2014, the song has sold 1,002,000 downloads in the US.<ref name=\"US Sales\">{{cite web | url =http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6221839/ask-billboard-iggy-azalea-ariana-grande-sam-smith-charli-xcx-are?page=0%2C2 | title = Ask Billboard: Iggy Azalea, Ariana Grande, Sam Smith & Charli XCX Are Seeing Double | author =Trust, Gary|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media| date =  August 19, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe song achieved greater success in Canada, peaking at thirty on the [[Canadian Hot 100]].<ref name=\"sc_Billboardcanadianhot100_Selena Gomez & The Scene\"/> The song also appeared on numerous European charts, peaking at seventy-eight in the [[UK Singles Chart|United Kingdom]],<ref name=\"UKchart\"/> fifty-six in [[Media Control Charts|Germany]],<ref name=germanchart/> and forty-one in [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry|Slovakia]].<ref name=\"sc_Slovakia_Selena Gomez\"/> It also reached number three on the [[Ultratop|Belgian Flanders Tip]] chart.<ref name=\"sc_Belgium (Flanders) Tip_Selena Gomez & The Scene\">{{cite web |url=http://unrealityshout.com/blogs/single-review-selena-gomez-the-scene-a-year-without-rain |title=Single Review: Selena Gomez & The Scene \u2013 'A Year Without Rain' |first=Dara |last=Hickey |publisher=Unreality Shout |accessdate=31 August 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101130052138/http://unrealityshout.com/blogs/single-review-selena-gomez-the-scene-a-year-without-rain |archive-date=2010-11-30 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Music videos==\nThe music video, directed by Chris Dooley, was shot on location in [[Lucerne Valley, California]].<ref name=\"press\">{{cite press release|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2010/08/27/disney-channel-to-present-premiere-of-selena-gomez-the-scenes-music-video-a-year-without-rain-friday-september-3/61274/|title=Disney Channel to Present Premiere of Selena Gomez & The Scene's Music Video \"A Year Without Rain,\" Friday, September 3|date=2010-08-27|publisher=[[Disney Channel]]|accessdate=2011-11-13}}</ref> It premiered on September 3, 2010 on [[Disney Channel]], following the premiere of ''[[Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam]]'' and a sneak peek of ''[[Fish Hooks]]''.<ref name=\"press\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1646535/20100826/gomez__selena.jhtml|title=Selena Gomez's 'A Year Without Rain' Video Premieres September 3|first=Jocelyn|last=Vena|work=[[MTV News]]|publisher=MTV Networks (Viacom)|accessdate=2010-12-27}}</ref> The video starts off with the band driving through the desert in a red convertible. Gomez removes a photograph from the sun visor, which is subsequently blown away by the wind. The chorus commences as the band disappears and Gomez steps out of the vehicle, wearing a dress and begins to sing. As the video progresses, a multitude of photographs of her relationship fall from the sky, as Gomez travels elegantly through the desert. During the bridge, it starts to rain as Gomez spots her love interest (Niko Pepaj) in the distance. The two begin to walk towards each other, and the video ends as they meet and hold hands.\n\nNadine Cheung of [[AOL|AOL JSYK]] said \"She sings: 'I'm missing you so much / Can't help it, I'm in love / A day without you is like a year without rain' and that's really what's depicted in a simple and sweet way.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jsyk.com/2010/09/06/selena-gomez-gets-soaked-in-her-a-year-without-rain-video/|title=Selena Gomez Gets Soaked In Her 'A Year Without Rain' Video|first=Nadine|last=Cheung|accessdate=2010-12-27|date=2010-09-06|work=[[AOL|AOL JSYK]]|publisher=AOL|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110207052121/http://www.jsyk.com/2010/09/06/selena-gomez-gets-soaked-in-her-a-year-without-rain-video|archive-date=2011-02-07|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nA Spanish version (\"Un A\u00f1o Sin Lluvia\") of the video was released on November 19 on [[Vevo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vaoPovB40dQ|title=Selena Gomez & the Scene \u2013 Un A\u00f1o Sin Lluvia|publisher=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n\n==Live performances==\nThe band first performed the song on September 22, 2010 on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]''.<ref name=\"Rosario\">{{cite web|url=http://www.latina.com/entertainment/music/selena-gomezs-new-album-year-without-rain-drops-today|title=Selena Gomez's New Album \"A Year Without Rain\" Drops Today!|work=[[Latina (magazine)|Latina]]|accessdate=2011-03-15|date=2010-09-21|first=Mariela|last=Rosario|publisher=Latina Media Ventures|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120401122827/http://www.latina.com/entertainment/music/selena-gomezs-new-album-year-without-rain-drops-today|archive-date=2012-04-01|url-status=dead}}</ref> The band performed the song on ''[[Good Morning America]]'' on September 23, 2010.<ref name=\"Rosario\"/> On November 16, 2010, the band performed the song on ''[[Lopez Tonight]]'', and they performed it on ''[[Live with Regis and Kelly]]'' on December 1, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lopeztonight.com/episode_recaps_and_highlights/selena_gomez_sings.php |title=Selena Gomez Really Has Had a Year Without Rain |work=Lopeztonight.com |publisher=[[Turner Broadcasting System]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722082823/http://www.lopeztonight.com/episode_recaps_and_highlights/selena_gomez_sings.php |archivedate=2011-07-22 }}</ref> They performed the song at the [[37th People's Choice Awards|2011 People's Choice Awards]] on January 5, 2011, and afterwards were awarded the Choice award for Favorite Breakout Artist.<ref name=\"Warner\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1655377/selena-gomez-peoples-choice-awards.jhtml|title=Selena Gomez Wows People's Choice Awards With 'A Year Without Rain'|work=[[MTV News]]|publisher=[[MTV Networks]] ([[Viacom (2005\u2013present)|Viacom]])|accessdate=2011-03-15|date=2011-01-05|first=Kara|last=Warner}}</ref> Gomez appeared on stage accompanied by low lights and fog.<ref name=\"Warner\"/> Kara Warner of [[MTV News]] commented, \"Although it wasn't a stadium-rocking performance \u00e0 la [[Lady Gaga]] or [[Katy Perry]], Gomez powered through her pop song with a sense of earnestness and commitment. She didn't even miss a beat when her earpiece appeared to fall out mid-song.\" The song was also performed during the \"[[We Own the Night Tour]]\".<ref name=\"Warner\"/>\n\n==Formats and track listings==\n*'''Germany CD single'''<ref name=\"CD\"/>\n#\"A Year Without Rain\" \u2013 3:54\n#\"A Year Without Rain\" (Starlab Radio Edit) \u2013 3:41\n\n*'''Digital download'''<ref name=\"Digital\"/>\n#\"A Year Without Rain\" \u2013 3:55\n\n*'''UK promo CD'''\n#\"A Year Without Rain\" \u2013 3:54\n#\"A Year Without Rain\" (Instrumental) \u2013 3:54\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits and personnel adapted from ''[[A Year Without Rain]]'' album liner notes.<ref name=\"Album liner notes\">{{cite AV media notes|others=Selena Gomez|title=[[A Year Without Rain]]|type=booklet|year=2010|publisher=[[Hollywood Records|Hollywood]]|id=D000462502}}</ref>\n* [[Selena Gomez]] \u2013 lead vocals\n* [[Lindy Robbins]] \u2013 songwriting\n* Robert Vosgien \u2013 mastering\n* [[Toby Gad]] \u2013 songwriting, production, mixing, arrangement, recording & instruments\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Award\n! scope=\"col\" | Category\n! scope=\"col\" | Work\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2011\n|rowspan=\"2\"|  MuchMusic Video Awards <ref>{{cite news | title=MuchMusic Video Award nominations: The full list | url=http://arts.nationalpost.com/2011/05/17/muchmusic-video-award-nominations-the-full-list/ | first=Angela | last=Hickman | date=May 17, 2011 | newspaper=[[National Post]] | accessdate=September 7, 2013 | archive-url=https://archive.is/20120702020957/http://arts.nationalpost.com/2011/05/17/muchmusic-video-award-nominations-the-full-list/ | archive-date=2012-07-02 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|\"International Video of the Year\"\n|rowspan=\"10\"| \"[[A Year Without Rain]]\"\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|\"UR FAVE International Artist\"\n|{{nom}}\n|}\n\n==Charts and certifications==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (2010\u201311)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n|Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://imgur.com/a/uXa0A|title=Response from ARIA re: chart inquiry, received 2017-01-20|publisher=imgur.com|accessdate=2017-01-20}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|78\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders Tip|3|artist=Selena Gomez & The Scene|song=A Year Without Rain}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardcanadianhot100|30|artist=Selena Gomez & The Scene|artistid={{BillboardID|Selena Gomez}}|song=A Year Without Rain}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|56|artist=Gomez, Selena & The Scene|song=A Year Without Rain (2-track)|songid=743025|accessdate=2019-02-22|refname=germanchart}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Czech Republic|41|year=2010|week=47}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Slovakia|41|artist=Selena Gomez|song=A year without rain|year=2010|week=45}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|78|date=20101120|artist=Selena Gomez & The Scene|song=A Year Without Rain|accessdate=2010-11-09|refname=UKchart}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardhot100|35|artist=Selena Gomez|artistid={{BillboardID|Selena Gomez}}|accessdate=2010-12-26|song=A Year Without Rain}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboarddanceclubplay|1|artist=Selena Gomez|artistid={{BillboardID|Selena Gomez}}|accessdate=2010-12-26|song=A Year Without Rain}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Certifications===\n{{certification Table Top}}\n{{certification Table Entry|type=single|region=United States|artist=Selena Gomez & The Scene|title=A Year Without Rain|award=Platinum{{sup|{{Dagger}}}}|number=2|salesamount=2,000,000||salesref=<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&se=A+year+without+rain#search_section|title=RIAA Certification|date=7 September 2018|access-date=7 September 2018}}</ref>}}\n{{certification Table Entry|region = Australia|artist = Selena Gomez & The Scene|title = A Year Without Rain|award = Gold|certyear=2011|type = single|access-date=Oct 13, 2011|digital=true|relyear=2011}}\n{{certification Table Bottom}}\n\n{{small|{{sup|{{Dagger}}}} Since May 9, 2013, RIAA certifications for digital singles include on-demand audio and/or video song streams in addition to downloads.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.riaa.com/newsitem.php?content_selector=riaa-news-gold-and-platinum&news_month_filter=5&news_year_filter=2013&id=C19496E7-CEC0-C453-D8A1-BD80E56E610F |title=RIAA Adds Digital Streams To Historic Gold & Platinum Awards |publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]] |date=May 9, 2013 |accessdate=May 9, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6GuWJIOEO?url=http://www.riaa.com/newsitem.php?content_selector=riaa-news-gold-and-platinum&news_month_filter=5&news_year_filter=2013&id=C19496E7-CEC0-C453-D8A1-BD80E56E610F |archivedate=May 26, 2013 }}</ref>}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:18.5em;\"| Chart (2011)\n!scope=\"col\"| Position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] ([[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']])<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2011/hot-dance-club-play-songs?begin=31&order=position |title=Best of 2011: Dance/Club Songs (31\u201340) |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |accessdate=May 1, 2012}}</ref>\n|35\n|-\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Region\n! Date\n! Format\n|-\n|Canada<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/a-year-without-rain/id387935992?i=387936000&ign-mpt=uo%3D2|title=A Year Without Rain \u2013 Single by 